@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About Us";
}

<style>
    .containerAboutsite {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 40px 20px;
        text-align: center;
        background-color: #f5f5f5;
    }

    h1 {
        font-size: 36px;
        font-weight: bold;
        margin-bottom: 30px;
    }

    p {
        font-size: 18px;
        line-height: 1.5;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
</style>

<div class="containerAboutsite">
    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
    <p>A photo gallery website is a platform designed to showcase a collection of images. The purpose of a photo gallery site is to allow visitors to view and appreciate photographs that have been curated and organized by the site's owner. These galleries can be organized by subject matter, theme, location, or other criteria.</p>
    <p>Our website aims to provide a space for photographers and creatives to share and showcase their work, connect with others, and inspire new ideas. We believe that everyone has a unique perspective and creative vision, and we want to celebrate and showcase that diversity.</p>
</div>
